    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Reidun/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Steamship <hi rend="italic">Reidun</hi> seized March 17 under Section 586
                    Tariff Act and 205 Anti-Smuggling Act. Four officers arrested same day charged
                    with conspiracy under Section 88 Title 18 United States Code in connection with
                    seizure smuggling vessel <hi rend="italic">Pronto</hi> off South Carolina. Part
                    of <hi rend="italic">Reidun</hi> cargo found on <hi rend="italic">Pronto</hi>
                    and part on wharf at Keansburg, New Jersey.</p>
                <p>The above is for your information as Norwegian Minister is making active
                    representations in the case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
